#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo Linux can be installed using a <e>stage3</e> tarball file.\n"
"Such a tarball is an archive that contains a minimal environment from\n"
"which you can succesfully install Gentoo Linux onto your system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:73
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Installations using a stage1 or stage2 tarball file are not documented in the\n"
"Gentoo Handbook - please read the <uri link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#stage12\">Gentoo\n"
"FAQ</uri> on these matters.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"An Installation CD is a bootable medium which contains a self-sustained Gentoo \n"
"environment. It allows you to boot Linux from the CD. During the boot process \n"
"your hardware is detected and the appropriate drivers are loaded. The Gentoo \n"
"Installation CDs are maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "There currently are two Installation CDs available:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:97
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Universal Installation CD contains everything you need to install \n"
"    Gentoo. It provides stage3 files for common architectures, source code \n"
"    for the extra applications you need to choose from and, of course, the \n"
"    installation instructions for your architecture.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Minimal Installation CD contains only a minimal environment that allows \n"
"    you to boot up and configure your network so you can connect to the \n"
"    Internet. It does not contain any additional files and cannot be used \n"
"    during the current installation approach.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:111
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo also provides a Package CD. This is not an Installation CD but an\n"
"additional resource that you can exploit during the installation of your Gentoo\n"
"system. It contains prebuilt packages (also known as the GRP set) that allow\n"
"you to easily and quickly install additional applications (such as\n"
"OpenOffice.org, KDE, GNOME, ...) immediately after the Gentoo installation and\n"
"right before you update your Portage tree.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "The use of the Package CD is covered later in this document. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot the Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:134
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can download the Universal Installation CD (and, if you want to, the \n"
"Packages CD as well) from one of our <uri \n"
"link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. The Installation CD is located in \n"
"the <path>releases/amd64/2006.0/installcd</path> directory;\n"
"the Package CD is located in the <path>releases/amd64/2006.0/packagecd</path>\n"
"directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside those directories you'll find ISO-files. Those are full CD images which\n"
"you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:148
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After downloading the file, you can verify its integrity to see if it is \n"
"corrupted or not:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:154
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we \n"
"    provide (for instance with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or \n"
"    <uri link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:159
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can verify the cryptographic signature that we provide. You need to\n"
"    obtain the public key we use (17072058) before you proceed though.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fetch our public key using the GnuPG application, run the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver subkeys.pgp.net --recv-keys 17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:181
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:189
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc &lt;downloaded iso\n"
"    file&gt;</c> (replace <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device\n"
"    path).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:203
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once you have burned your installation CDs, it is time to boot them.\n"
"Remove all CDs from the CD drives, reboot your system and enter the BIOS. \n"
"This is usually done by hitting DEL, F1\n"
"or ESC, depending on your BIOS. Inside the BIOS, change the boot\n"
"order so that the CD-ROM is tried before the hard disk. This is often found\n"
"under \"CMOS Setup\". If you don't do this, your system will just reboot from the \n"
"hard disk, ignoring the CD-ROM.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:217
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now place the installation CD in the CD-ROM drive and reboot. You\n"
"should see a boot prompt. At this\n"
"screen, you can hit Enter to begin the boot process with the default\n"
"boot options, or boot the Installation CD with custom boot options by specifying\n"
"a kernel followed by boot options and then hitting Enter. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:225
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Specifying a kernel? Yes, we provide several kernels on our Installation CD. The\n"
"default one is <c>gentoo</c>. Other kernels are for specific hardware needs and\n"
"the <c>-nofb</c> variants which disable framebuffer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "Below you'll find a short overview on the available kernels:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:236
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:237
#, no-wrap
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "gentoo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:241
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default kernel with support for K8 CPUs with NUMA"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:246
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can also provide kernel options. They represent optional settings\n"
"you can (de)activate at will. The following code listing explains all available\n"
"kernel options.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "Available boot options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- agpgart       loads agpgart (use if you have graphic problems,lockups)\n"
"- acpi=on       loads support for ACPI firmware\n"
"- ide=nodma     force disabling of DMA for malfunctioning IDE devices\n"
"- doscsi        scan for scsi devices (breaks some ethernet cards)\n"
"- dopcmcia      starts pcmcia service for PCMCIA cdroms\n"
"- nofirewire    disables firewire modules in initrd (for firewire cdroms,etc)\n"
"- nokeymap      disables keymap selection for non-us keyboard layouts\n"
"- docache       cache the entire runtime portion of cd in RAM, allows you\n"
"                to umount /mnt/cdrom to mount another cdrom.\n"
"- nodetect      causes hwsetup/kudzu and hotplug not to run\n"
"- nousb         disables usb module load from initrd, disables hotplug\n"
"- nodhcp        dhcp does not automatically start if nic detected\n"
"- nohotplug     disables loading hotplug service\n"
"- noapic        disable apic (try if having hardware problems nics,scsi,etc)\n"
"- noevms2       disable loading of EVMS2 modules\n"
"- nolvm2        disable loading of LVM2 modules\n"
"- hdx=stroke    allows you to partition the whole harddrive even when your BIOS\n"
"                can't handle large harddrives\n"
"- noload=module1[,module2[,...]]\n"
"                disable loading of specific kernel modules\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:275
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now boot your CD, select a kernel (if you are not happy with the default\n"
"<c>gentoo</c> kernel) and boot options. As an example, we show you how\n"
"to boot the <c>gentoo</c> kernel, with <c>dopcmcia</c> as kernel\n"
"parameters:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting an Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:282
#, no-wrap
msgid "boot: <i>gentoo dopcmcia</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:286
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You will then be greeted with a boot screen and progress bar. If you are\n"
"installing Gentoo on a system with a non-US keyboard, make sure you\n"
"immediately press Alt-F1 to switch to verbose mode and follow the prompt. If no\n"
"selection is made in 10 seconds, the default (US keyboard) will be accepted and\n"
"the boot process will continue. Once the boot process completes, you will be\n"
"automatically logged in to the \"Live\" Gentoo Linux as\n"
"\"root\", the super user. You should have a root (\"#\") prompt\n"
"on the current console and can also switch to other consoles by pressing Alt-F2,\n"
"Alt-F3 and Alt-F4. Get back to the one you started on by pressing Alt-F1.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:298
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now continue with <uri link=\"#hardware\">Extra Hardware \n"
"Configuration</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:305
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extra Hardware Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the Installation CD boots, it tries to detect all your hardware devices and\n"
"loads the appropriate kernel modules to support your hardware. In the\n"
"vast majority of cases, it does a very good job. However, in some cases it may \n"
"not auto-load the kernel modules you need. If the PCI auto-detection missed \n"
"some of your system's hardware, you will have to load the appropriate kernel \n"
"modules manually. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the next example we try to load the <c>8139too</c> module (support for \n"
"certain kinds of network interfaces):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:322
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading kernel modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe 8139too</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:327
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you need PCMCIA support, you should start the <c>pcmcia</c> init script:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:330
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the PCMCIA init script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/pcmcia start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:337
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Tweaking Hard Disk Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:341
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are an advanced user, you might want to tweak the IDE hard disk\n"
"performance using <c>hdparm</c>. With the <c>-tT</c> options you can\n"
"test the performance of your disk (execute it several times to get a\n"
"more precise impression):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:347
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:348
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:352
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To tweak, you can use any of the following examples (or experiment\n"
"yourself) which use <path>/dev/hda</path> as disk (substitute with your\n"
"disk):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:357
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tweaking hard disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:358
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>Activate DMA:</comment>                                       # <i>hdparm -d 1 /dev/hda</i>\n"
"<comment>Activate DMA + Safe Performance-enhancing Options:</comment>  # <i>hdparm -d 1 -A 1 -m 16 -u 1 -a 64 /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:365
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: User Accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:369
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you plan on giving other people access to your installation\n"
"environment or you want to chat using <c>irssi</c> without root privileges (for\n"
"security reasons), you need to create the necessary user accounts and change \n"
"the root password.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:376
#, no-wrap
msgid "To change the root password, use the <c>passwd</c> utility:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>passwd</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter your new password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter your password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:386
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To create a user account, we first enter their credentials, followed by\n"
"its password. We use <c>useradd</c> and <c>passwd</c> for these tasks.\n"
"In the next example, we create a user called &quot;john&quot;.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:391
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a user account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-amd64-medium.xml:392
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>useradd -m -G users john</i>\n"
